  "text": "Stack protection mechanisms in LLVM are implemented across multiple components:\n\n## 1. StackProtector Pass (Buffer Overflow Protection)\n\nThe primary stack protection mechanism against buffer overflow attacks is implemented in:\n- **Header**: `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/StackProtector.h` - Declares `StackProtectorPass`, `StackProtector`, `SSPLayoutAnalysis`, and `SSPLayoutInfo`\n- **Implementation**: `llvm/lib/CodeGen/StackProtector.cpp` - The core `StackProtector` class (FunctionPass) that inserts stack protectors and the `StackProtectorPass` (PassInfoMixin) for the new PM\n\nThis pass inserts a random canary value onto the stack before local variables are allocated. Upon function exit (specifically before return instructions), it verifies the canary hasn't been corrupted. If it has, it calls `__stack_chk_fail()`.\n\n## 2. SafeStack Pass (Stack Separation)\n\nThe SafeStack pass separates safe and unsafe stack allocations:\n- **Header**: `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SafeStack.h` - Declares `SafeStackPass`\n- **Implementation**: `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SafeStack.cpp` - Contains both `SafeStack` class and `SafeStackLegacyPass`\n- **Layout Helper**: `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SafeStackLayout.h/cpp` - Implements `StackLayout` class for computing unsafe stack frame layout\n\nSafeStack partitions the stack into a safe stack (only accessed through memory-safe dereferences) and an unsafe stack (containing variables that cannot be proven safe), providing additional protection against stack-based attacks.\n\n## 3. Runtime Support\n\n### Stack Canary Failure Handler\n- **Header**: `libc/src/compiler/__stack_chk_fail.h` - Declares `__stack_chk_fail()` function\n- **Implementation**: `libc/src/compiler/generic/__stack_chk_fail.cpp` - Implements `__stack_chk_fail()` which writes \"stack smashing detected\" to stderr and calls `abort()`\n- **Guard Variable**: Also defines `__stack_chk_guard` (default value: 0xa9fff01234)\n\n### SafeStack Runtime\n- **Main Implementation**: `compiler-rt/lib/safestack/safestack.cpp` - Implements runtime support managing allocation/deallocation of the unsafe stack for the main thread and pthreads\n- **Platform Abstraction**: `compiler-rt/lib/safestack/safestack_platform.h` - Platform-specific syscall wrappers (Linux, FreeBSD, NetBSD, Solaris)\n- **Utilities**: `compiler-rt/lib/safestack/safestack_util.h` - Helper functions for SafeStack runtime\n\n## 4. Stack Checking (Allocation Guards)\n\nWhile distinct from stack protection against buffer overflow, LLVM also provides stack checking for large allocations (Windows-specific):\n- **x86_64**: `compiler-rt/lib/builtins/x86_64/chkstk.S` - `___chkstk_ms` routine\n- **x86/i386**: `compiler-rt/lib/builtins/i386/chkstk.S`, `chkstk2.S`\n- **ARM**: `compiler-rt/lib/builtins/arm/chkstk.S`\n- **AArch64**: `compiler-rt/lib/builtins/aarch64/chkstk.S`\n\nThese routines probe stack pages to ensure guard pages are not skipped during large stack allocations.\n\n## Integration\n\nBoth passes are registered in the code generation pipeline via `llvm/include/llvm/Passes/CodeGenPassBuilder.h`, where they are added as function passes in the appropriate order during machine code generation."
